Testing and Documentation Rule
Testing expectations
Every new business logic path must have unit tests.
Bug fixes should include regression tests when practical.
UI work should include tests for meaningful user-visible behavior.
Prefer deterministic tests with clear Arrange / Act / Assert structure.
Mock only true boundaries, not internal behavior unnecessarily.

Documentation expectations
Every implementation must include concise documentation covering:
what was implemented
why it was implemented
how to run or use it
how it is tested
assumptions and tradeoffs
follow-up work if any

Preferred workflow
Describe expected behavior
Add or update tests
Implement
Re-run and verify
Document

Do not
skip tests for core logic
leave undocumented APIs or flows
claim something is verified without testing
